OL,3,CMan avoids jail after encouraging XL
OL,4,CBully to attack police officer
OL,6,FA police sergeant later caught up with
OL,7,Fhim, grabbing Wardle by the shoulder
OL,8,Fbut he broke free, telling the dogs to
OL,9,F"get" the officer who suffered an arm
OL,10,Finjury when he was bitten.
OL,12,FAnthony Pettengel, prosecuting, told
OL,13,Fthe court: "He ordered the dogs to
OL,14,Fattack the officer.
OL,16,F"The dogs became agitated. Most of the
OL,17,Fbites were to his padded jacket,
OL,18,Ffortunately, but one punctured his
OL,19,Fright upper arm."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
