OL,3,CMan avoids jail after encouraging XL
OL,4,CBully to attack police officer
OL,6,FHe was taken to the police van but
OL,7,Fwhile the doors were open he managed
OL,8,Fto break free before being detained
OL,9,Fagain. He later denied setting the
OL,10,Fdogs on the officer.
OL,12,FThe sergeant who was bitten said in a
OL,13,Fvictim impact statement he had never
OL,14,Fexperienced such an attack, which he
OL,15,Fbranded "disgraceful and
OL,16,Freprehensible". He was left worried
OL,17,Fand fearful about the consequences of
OL,18,Fbeing bitten by the dog.
OL,20,FWardle was bailed, failed to attend
OL,21,Fcourt then was bailed again.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/9
