OL,6,FIn a later incident on 26 November
OL,7,Fwhile still on bail, Wardle said he
OL,8,Fhad taken ecstasy. He was searched and
OL,9,Ffound to have a hunting knife and a
OL,10,Fcatapult. He was released on bail but
OL,11,Fthen failed to attend another court
OL,12,Fhearing.
OL,14,FWardle, who has 19 previous
OL,15,Fconvictions, pleaded guilty to assault
OL,16,Foccasioning actual bodily harm in
OL,17,Frelation to the dog attack, possessing
OL,18,Fa bladed article and two offences of
OL,19,Ffailing to attend court.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/9
